FBIS4-52295 "dreas089_c_94036" FBIS-EAS-94-089 Daily Report 7 May 1994 North Korea Communist Party of India Delegation Arrives Communist Party of India Delegation Arrives SK0805011494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1511 GMT 7 May 94 SK0805011494 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, May 7 (KCNA) -- A delegation of the Communist Party of India (Marxist) headed by Jyoti Basu, member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the party and prime minister of the West Bengal state, arrived here today. It was met at the airport by Hwang Chang-yop, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK], and Kim Yang-kon, vice department director of the Central Committee of the WPK, and Shehkholen Kipgen, Indian ambassador to Korea.
